</h3><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-29_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);"></span>Bleeding is a leading cause of preventable death after injury. Approximately 35% of pre-hospital deaths are due to blood loss, and controlling this bleeding early can significantly improve survival rates. In workplaces, mainly where machinery or high-risk activities are involved, the knowledge of managing bleeding is essential.


